    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="426"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d426">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 342.112Sm6/a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">British Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 28, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: We have just received the
                    following despatch from our Vice Consul at Bridgeburg, Ontario: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Walter Smith, Buffalo N. Y., shot and killed; Charles Dorsch, Buffalo, N.
                            Y., shot through lung by private in Canadian militia in Fort Erie this
                            morning. These men were duck shooting and did not land when ordered.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>This confirms the report given in the newspapers. Will you please bring the
                    matter at once to the attention of your Government and secure a report on the
                    same?</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
